        By plane - wikitravel
    
        Lapu-Lapu City is located in Mactan Island, Cebu, Philippines, so the fastest way to get to Lapu-Lapu City, Cebu, Philippines is by air. The Mactan-Cebu International Airport is located in Lapu-Lapu City where foreign visitors, local visitors and residents may fly direct to Cebu from Dubai, Hong Kong, Singapore, Taipei, Tokyo, Seoul, Kuala Lumpur, Bangkok thru this airport. International flight from budget carriers also flying direct to this airport from Singapore, Hong Kong, Kuala Lumpur, Taiwan and Japan. Facilities and amenities include a shopping center, duty-free shop, souvenir shops, cafés, business centers, food shops, communication facilities, banking facilities, car rentals, hotel and resort reservations, beauty & health services.
    
        Cathay Pacific Airways, Philippine Airlines (the Philippine's flag carrier) and Cebu Pacific, a budget carrier, fly between Hong Kong and Cebu daily while Air Asia, Scoot Air, Silkair and Cebu pacific fly between Cebu and Singapore. Philippine Airlines fly between Cebu-Tokyo daily except Mondays and Cebu-Seoul daily, Air Asia fly daily from Cebu to Kuala Lumpur . Emirates Airlines meanwhile fly from Dubai to Cebu. Visitors may also pass through via Seoul-Incheon as Asiana Airlines, Cebu Pacific, Philippine Airlines and Korean Air all fly to Korea. Taipei is another point of entry as China Airlines / Mandarin Airlines have flights to Cebu.
    
        Lapu-Lapu City is also the domestic air hub of the Philippines with close to 60 flights daily on average to and from popular destinations and key cities all over the archipelago such as Manila, Kalibo, Puerto Princesa, Boracay, Clark, Siargao (Surigao), Zamboanga, Davao, Bacolod, Iloilo, Cagayan de Oro, Camiguin, General Santos, and Leyte.
    
        Visitors from North America, Europe, Middle East, and the rest of the world may fly first to Shanghai or Singapore or Hong Kong or Seoul or Taipei to catch a flight to Lapu-Lapu City. There are also flights to Lapu-Lapu City from Clark or Davao or Kalibo International airports, from which there are further flights on discount airlines to Macau, Kuala Lumpur and Singapore and other points.
    
        Charter flights are also available in some select destinations especially China, Korea and Taiwan.
    
    
